# Multi Vendor Inventory API

A backend service built with **FastAPI** and **MongoDB** that manages stock items, vendors, and purchase orders.
The system supports linking multiple vendors to stock items and ensures that purchase orders can only be created with approved vendors.

---

## Features

* Stock Item Management (CRUD)
* Vendor Management (CRUD)
* Item ↔ Vendor relationship (Many-to-Many)
* Purchase Order creation with validation
* Async MongoDB operations
* Clean service-layer architecture

---

## Tech Stack

* **Python**
* **FastAPI**
* **MongoDB**
* **Motor (Async Mongo Driver)**
* **Uvicorn**

---

## Setup Instructions

### 1. Clone the Repository

```bash
git clone <https://github.com/itzmevicky/inventory_management.git>
cd inventory_management

```

---

### 2. Create a Virtual Environment

```bash
python -m venv venv
```

Activate it:

**Windows**

```bash
venv\Scripts\activate
```

**Linux / Mac**

```bash
source venv/bin/activate
```

---

### 3. Install Dependencies

```bash
pip install -r requirements.txt
```

---



### 4. Run the FastAPI Server

```bash
uvicorn app.main:app --reload
```

---

## Access the API

Once the server starts, you can access:

Interactive API Docs (Swagger):

```
http://127.0.0.1:8000/docs
```
---

## API Overview

### Items

```
POST   /items
GET    /items
GET    /items/{item_id}
PATCH  /items/{item_id}
DELETE /items/{item_id}
```

### Vendors

```
POST   /vendors
GET    /vendors
GET    /vendors/{vendor_id}
PATCH  /vendors/{vendor_id}
DELETE /vendors/{vendor_id}
```

### Item-Vendor Relationships

```
POST   /items/{item_id}/vendors/{vendor_id}
GET    /items/{item_id}/vendors
GET    /vendors/{vendor_id}/items
DELETE /items/{item_id}/vendors/{vendor_id}
```

### Purchase Orders

```
POST   /purchase-orders
GET    /purchase-orders
GET    /purchase-orders/{po_id}
```

Purchase orders can only be created if the **vendor is linked to the item**.

